(2) Without limiting the generality of subsection (1), regulations under this section may be made for or with respect to— (a) the appointment to office, including the power to confirm appointments, of the staff of the Judicature and such of the members of the Judicature as are appointed by the Commission ; (b) promotions to such offices; (c) the disciplinary control of persons holding or acting in such offices. (d) the termination of appointments and the removal of such persons from office; (e) prescribing the qualifications for appointment or promotion to any post; (f) the transfer or secondment of any person holding any such office; and (g) such training courses as may be considered necessary for promoting or maintaining efficiency.
